Sarah and her truck on large format film in some south Austin field at sunset. We kicked things off by getting her truck stuck in a ditch while trying to park it in this pretty field! Luckily we were roughly one firm-kick-of-a-soccer-ball’s distance from a Lowe’s where I bought a towing cable and an even shorter distance from local hero Timothy who helped us tow the thing out. Then Timothy, god bless him, pointed about 50 feet down the road where there was a straight up driveway leading into the field that we’d somehow overlooked. Anyway if anyone finds themselves stuck in a ditch, I’ve got a cable!

It should be mandatory that people take classes where they learn the fundamentals of firearms before ever purchasing and owning them. I highly recommend training with @falken_firearms_training . She’s a badass with a wealth of knowledge. #beginner #lonestarstate

Facebook reminded me of this first photo which was taken in Hawaii 10 years ago😳. I look at this photo and think, “she is still the same girl” but the thoughts and feelings that arise with (a decade ago) sent me unraveling. How quickly time slips away from right under us…How I used to long for time to speed up when I was younger and now I just yearn for it to slow down. Here is a carousel of memories that are new but are intrinsically old in routine, comfort and familiarity… 🫶🏼 #ontheroadagain #la
